# Cloudflare Pages supports Netlify-style _redirects.
#
# Important:
# - Keep redirects path-based and safe.
# - Domain-level redirects (e.g. steady-plan.co.uk -> steadyplan.co.uk) should be configured in Cloudflare (Redirect Rules / Bulk Redirects),
#   not here.

/index.html           /                301

# Canonical paths (avoid duplicate content / convenience)
/docs                 /docs/            301
/docs/index.html      /docs/            301

# Do not redirect clean doc URLs (for example /docs/install) to .html files.
# Cloudflare Pages serves extensionless URLs and may redirect .html back to the
# clean path, so adding /docs/install -> /docs/install.html can create a loop.
